the logarithmic scatter in the stellar mass at fixed halo mass and the
slope of the mean SHMR at high masses, without assuming a strong prior
on the scatter and/or using the SMF as an input. We detect a decline of
the scatter with halo mass, from 0.22\_\{-0.01\}\^\{+0.02\} dex below
1012 h-1 M$\odot$ to 0.18 $\pm$ 0.01
dex at 1014 h-1 M$\odot$. The model
predicts a departure of satellite SMFs from the Schechter form in
massive haloes and a linear scaling of satellite number with halo mass.
